We‚Äôre psyched to announce ‚ÄúSupporting Figures‚Äù our latest edition and second collaboration with @jchapline Chapline's unique aesthetic blurs the lines between an intangible digital realm and the reality of the analogue world, finding poetry in the contrast. When working with Case Studyo, Jonathan avidly seizes the opportunity of introducing his fantastical, otherworldly universe into the microcosm of our homes.  For this edition, Chapline further explores a beloved, recurring theme in his work; the human form. By deconstructing his subjects into abstract flat shapes and reassembling them to compose new volumes, the artist manages to evoke the surreal experience of existential passion harnessed in digital form. A deliberate and bold choice of materials emphasises the inherent contradiction in his work; infusing cold steel with raw emotion. The edition consists of 2 metal figures carefully welded and powder coated in Telemagenta and Ultramarine with a silky smooth satin finish.
Standalone sculptures or utility objects, these 'Supporting Figures' are ready to be welcomed into your home. Each sculpture stands 30cm/12inch tall and comes in an edition of 25 each. For further info and inquiries visit casestudyo.com 
#jonathanchapline #supportingfigures #sculpture #edition #casestudyo

This special Season 3 finale of #TalkArtPodcast is an interview with the late, great, legendary artist Joyce Pensato @joycepensato. Joyce was one of Russell & Robert‚Äôs favourite painters, who in recent years became a close friend to both. We were honoured to be invited by Joyce to visit her in New York on 28th May 2019 to record what became her last interview. We discuss growing up in #Brooklyn, the encouragement of her father (an outsider artist who often made her toys), her love of #GermanExpressionism in her teens but also #Gauguin and #VanGogh, of whom she made a clay sculpture of which she would carry on the subway to show people. Joyce explains how Hollywood movies & pop culture had a lasting impact on her work, her love of #ConeyIsland, meeting fellow painter #ChristopherWool, painting with black & white enamel paint, how Christopher‚Äôs father Ira Wool became the first champion and collector of her paintings followed by exhibitions in Paris and further support from French collectors. She discusses a recent sculpture inspired by #BigAng (the US mafia ‚ÄúMob moll‚Äù and reality TV star), her love of the movie #Rocky and how #SylvesterStallone began collecting her work, why she had a nickname of ‚ÄòThe Eraser‚Äô, her beloved dog Charlie, her key 1970s mentors & painting teachers #MercedesMatter and #JoanMitchell, how #TheaWestreich championed her work in the 80s, her love of the works of #GeorgGrosz, #EdvardMunch and #FrancisBacon. We also chat with artist #ElizabethFerry @elizabethferry who ran Joyce‚Äôs studio for the past ten years and hear how they became known collectively as The Fizz & The Cucumber!!! Joyce set up the ‚ÄòJoyce Pensato Foundation‚Äô to support future generations of young artists. We love you Joyce! #TheFizzisFizzing!! ‚ÄúI feel like I‚Äôm in the painting. We are one. I totally love to be physical. It‚Äôs in me.‚Äù Joyce Pensato, 1941-2019. üì∏Photo credit: Credit: Tony Cenicola for New York Times

We‚Äôre happy and pleased to present our final edition for 2019. Signing off with a bang in collaboration with Brooklyn based artist Katie Stout @ummmsmile ‚ÄòSlouchy Slue‚Äô & ‚ÄòSlouchy Slurple‚Äô showcase Stout‚Äôs unique take on household objects, transcending both traditional home furnishing and sculptural work alike. Stout likes to experiment with different techniques, mixing low-brow and accessible materials. For this edition, Case Studyo and Katie Stout set out to explore uncharted territory, combining ceramic plaster and rubber to create a set of otherworldly table lamps.The fun, almost fungal like forms shed a new, unseen light on the concept of household objects. The two lamps represent an invitation to the user‚Äôs own private party, an everyday reminder to celebrate life every day. The lamp stands at 38 cm tall and each color way comes in an edition of 20. For further info and inquiries visit casestudyo.com

We‚Äôre pleased to announce ‚ÄòERODED SWEATSHIRT‚Äô a translucent sculptural porcelain lamp by Daniel Arsham @danielarsham :
The Case Studyo x Arsham Studio ERODED SWEATSHIRT is a scaled-down porcelain version of a heavyweight pullover hooded sweatshirt, reminiscent of Arsham‚Äôs iconic eroded jacket sculptures. The eroded porcelain object references a distant future in which the sweatshirt has been excavated by archeologists. ERODED SWEATSHIRT reimagines the iconic piece of culture into an archaeological relic of the past, blending time and space. This merging of past and future asks the collector to consider the present moment as they turn the light on inside the porcelain form. Measuring 31.75 cm x 35.56 cm, this functional art object comes with a cool white LED light, hand numbered and signed COA cards, and Arsham Studio Standard art handling gloves. For info and inquires visit www.casestudyo.com

We‚Äôre happy to announce ‚ÄòTHEM‚Äô our latest collaboration with @jean_jullien For this edition Jean jullien introduces a colourful cast of beachgoers Lili, Vivi & Bruno as part of his ‚ÄòLesconil‚Äô series first seen @nanzukaunderground paying homage to the French port town Plobannalec-Lesconil where Jean‚Äôs family originates. Drawing from his childhood memories, the artist conjures 3 characters that could be seen at the picturesque white beaches of Lesconil. Each figure carries a specific type of fish, not merely as an accessory but as an extension of their personality. The nautical companions are more than pets, they represent the character‚Äôs spirit animals. The sculptures are made of cnc cut stainless steel in an edition of 50 and painstakingly screen printed to ensure the most vibrant color palette evoking the typical beach tones of Lesconil. We are pleased to announce ‚ÄúUNTITLED‚Äù a bronze sculpture by Susan Te Kahurangi King @susantekahurangiking an expert draughtsperson and unique image maker. Never using an eraser, her drawings show great immediacy, every mark on paper both confident and well-defined. As a self-taught and contemporary artist, Susan expresses her thoughts, fears, delights and fascinations, often incorporating elements from popular culture. It is remarkable that it‚Äôs only in recent years her vast body of work, or at least a small proportion of it, has come to light. She has a way of communicating that will challenge you to rethink the way you see the world.
---
For this collaboration, Case Studyo selected an image from works exhibited to date. The chosen drawing, circa 1959, depicts a contorted figure twisted into itself. The abstraction is instantly recognisable as Donald Duck, the beloved protagonist that has played a role in many childhood memories. Working closely with Susan‚Äôs family, Case Studyo carefully translated the drawing into a three dimensional sculpture with the utmost respect for Susan‚Äôs compelling visual language. The resulting seminal bronze sculpture celebrates the unique work of an inspiring and astounding artist.
Bronze ‚Äì white patina and hand painted details / 22cm.-8.6‚Äù /Edition of 8. 
Visit casestudyo.com or contact@casestudyo.com for inquiries and availability.
